now places like Sicily, I think it does get pretty hot, probably like high 30s? Yeah, yeah, so and I think the winters are probably quite mild, unless you’re from the North of Italy of course, near the mountains. Aimee: Yeah. Paul: Down in the south it remains kind of pretty mild, you know? Aimee: Aha, if it’s in the Med ... It''s my images of that. I’ve never been to Italy so I don’t know. I’ve been to the South of France and it got really hot. That was a nice temperature. It was dry, and yeah the nighttime wasn’t too hot either, it was really nice during the day. That was a nice climate, I think.', '{"difficulty_code": "C1", "duration_type": "conversations", "source": "downloaded_dataset"}', 'en-US', 'Switzerland, Scotland', 180, '2024-01-01 00:00:00', '2024-01-01 00:00:00', 1, 1, 0);
